 Chalk it up to campaign stress: ghosts are talking to Mayor <PERSON> Edward </PERSON> <PERSON> I. </PERSON> <PERSON> Koch </PERSON>, and he's talking back. <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Moses </PERSON>, <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>'s planning czar who died in 1981, recently stopped by to chat with <PERSON> Koch </PERSON>, the mayor said Monday. <PERSON> Koch </PERSON>, in the middle of a tough primary contest for his fourth term, said <PERSON> Moses </PERSON> relayed two requests. `` First, he wants me to be mayor,'' <PERSON> Koch </PERSON> said. The second request was that <PERSON> Koch </PERSON> bring the World's Fair to <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> sometime in the mid-1990s, he said. <PERSON> Koch </PERSON> was speaking to a black tie crowd attending a 50th anniversary celebration of the 1939 <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> World </ORGANIZATION>'s Fair. <PERSON> Koch </PERSON> reported that he told <PERSON> Moses </PERSON>, `` If I did n't see him in person between now and then, I'll do it.''
