shares, or 0.37 percent of the preferred shares outstanding, according to the filing. Under SEC rules, `` <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> H. </PERSON> <PERSON> Steinhardt </PERSON> may be deemed to own beneficially the shares of preferred stock owned'' by all three which `` constitute approximately 6.9 percent of the shares outstanding,'' according to the filing document. <PERSON> Steinhardt </PERSON> Parners purchased 23,982 shares at $ 11 per share for a total of $ 215,600 between May 19 and August 16, the filing stated. During that same period, SP International purchased 26,270, also for $ 11 per share, or $ 234,300 total, and <ORGANIZATION> GamCan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ltd. </ORGANIZATION> bought 3,109 shares at between $ 10.80 and $ 11 per share, for a total of $ 28,580. The filing, an amendment to one filed in April, did not specify the purpose of the stock purchases.
